Utterances.UttText: Subjective: CC: Chest pain HPI:  Ms.
Cage is a 55-year-old female who presents 3 days after an episode of chest pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: 3 days after an episode of chest pain.

Utterances.UttText: She reported that she was carrying groceries when she began to feel a deep squeezing midline pressure.
She reported that the pain did not radiate and that she was able to get full relief after sitting in her car quietly for 5-10 minutes.

Phrases.PhraseText: in her car quietly for 5-10 minutes.

Utterances.UttText: She also reported roughly a 4 month history of similar episodes that occurred during physical exertion and all of which resolved with rest.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 4 month history of similar episodes

Utterances.UttText: This most recent episode was the worst, which prompted her visit today.
She also endorsed feelings short of breath and faint during these episodes.

Phrases.PhraseText: She also endorsed feelings short of breath

Utterances.UttText: She denied dizziness, heart palpitations or nausea during the episodes.
Allergies: None Medications: Chlorthalidone for HTN.
Lisinopril for HTN.
PMHx: HTN FHx: Father - hx of CABG in 30s.
Died from MI at 40.
Mother - DM and died of PE at 60.
SHx: EtOH: Wine on weekends.
Tob: 1 PPD.
Drugs: Denies   Objective: BP= 150 /92 P = 85 RR = 14 T = 98F  Assessment: Ms.
Cage is a 55-year-old female who presents 3 days after an acute episode of chest pain during exertion that resolved completely with rest after 5-10 mins.

Phrases.PhraseText: 3 days after an acute episode of chest pain

Utterances.UttText: This is most likely stable angina given the patient's subjective report of typical chest pain symptoms with complete resolution with rest.

Phrases.PhraseText: the patient's subjective report of typical chest pain symptoms

Utterances.UttText: Significant concerns for progression given her reported history of the most recent episode being the worst.

Phrases.PhraseText: her reported history of the most recent episode

Utterances.UttText: Given her family history of heart disease in her father, there remains concerns for familial inherited dyslipidemia.

Phrases.PhraseText: her family history of heart disease

Utterances.UttText: Her history of smoking is also concerning for contribution to the disease progression.

Utterances.UttText: Her hypertension also seems to be uncontrolled and will warrant further workup.
Will make contact with PCP for medication adjsutment.
